Rating: 3
This was a very tasty cake. Not too sweet. I did not have vanilla bean so I used about 3/4 tsp of vanilla. I wish I had used more. Also I might decrease the baking time on this a little. Mine was in for about 40 minutes before I took it out. The edges were very dark brown. Despite this, the inside of the cake turned out well. I think I will try the Frengelico whipped cream next time.

Rating: 4
This got wows from all guests at my dinner party. I took tips from other reviewers--since I had no vanilla bean, I used 2 tsp. of vanilla extract (regular, not double strength), and I also wanted to use frangelico in the garnish. I whipped some cream up, and then beat in a bit of frangelico. I didn't measure, but it was just enough so that you could lightly taste it in the richness of the cream. I left it unsweetened. I also candied some hazelnuts with a simple water-sugar mix. When serving time came, I dolloped the frangelico-whipped cream in several spots around the edge of the cake, and topped each one with a candied hazelnut. It was gorgeous and the cake was delicious. Mine also turned very brown, which scared me a bit, but the cake inside was a normal color and incredibly moist. (I was really surprised by the latter attribute). In any case, it got rave reviews. I will definitely be making this again!!!

